Center: OECD/NEA Nuclear Data Bank, Boulogne-Billancourt, France
title: Inelastic scattering of 185 MeV protons from light nuclei.

x4freetext: Inelastic scattering of 185 MeV protons from light
subent 022--value E-exc-min and E-exc-mas was changed,
The boron powder was packed in containers of mylar
foils,25 mum thick.The same thickness of foils was used
for the water targets which were surrounded by a second
layer of mylar foils to prevent vacuum leaks.By using
ordinary and heavy water as O-16 targets in different
angular regions the peak due to scattering from
hydrogen or deuterium did not cause difficulties in
resolving the inelastic peaks from oxygen.The 5 mm
Li-6 target was wrapped in Al foils,50 mum thick.
The incident beam is monitored with a counter
telescope,which consist of two plastic scintillation
.The overall uncertainty in the absolute cross
sections becomes about 10%, slightly less for
Li-6,Be-9,C-12 and O-16 and slightly more for Li-7,B-10

x4freetext: The Statistical Errors are Comparable to or Smaller
Than the Size of the Experimental Points.
